post_text:
On Saturday, 2/22/2020, the Science Olympiad team from WPHS-North competed at Madison Central.
Congratulations to the following for their wins in Middle School Grades:

*Abby White & Hannah Smith 3rd place in Anatomy & Physiology;
*Dray Thompon & Phillip Andrews 3rd in Circuit Lab;
*Abby White & Brady Gaskin 2nd in Density Lab;
*Everyanna Quinn & Brady Gaskin 3rd in Disease Detectives;
*Hannah Smith & Malynn Shurden 2nd in Dynamic Planet;
*Hannah Smith & Everyanna Quinn 2nd in Elastic Launch Glider;
*Malynn Shurden & Dray Thompson 3rd in Fossils;
*Phillip Andrews & Brady Gaskin 2nd in Mousetrap Vehicle;
*Everyanna Quinn & Abby White 2nd in Water Quality;
*Abby White & Hannah Smith 1st in Write It Do It.

West Point High School-North won 3rd place overall for Middle School.

These students will advance to state competition on April 3rd at USM in Hattiesburg.

Ms. Fulgham & Ms. Zimmerman are super proud of these students for their accomplishments and sportsmanship.

